you can't mistake it for whooping cough.

959
01:18:57,032 --> 01:18:59,330
His doctor says he died from encephalitis.

960
01:18:59,401 --> 01:19:02,165
- It's on his death certificate.
- Let's talk to the doctor.

961
01:19:02,270 --> 01:19:04,602
And get him to say what? He lied?

962
01:19:04,673 --> 01:19:07,039
Somewhere in town,
there must be somebody.

963
01:19:07,142 --> 01:19:10,236
A gay man he had sex with or...
Does his family know?

964
01:19:12,948 --> 01:19:14,779
My brother wasn't gay.

965
01:19:15,016 --> 01:19:17,280
No matter how hard you search...

966
01:19:17,352 --> 01:19:20,321
...you won't find any evidence
to suggest the contrary.

967
01:19:21,123 --> 01:19:23,318
He was on the board
of several corporations.

968
01:19:23,391 --> 01:19:26,656
He was the chairman of the Fundraising
Committee for St. Patrick's.

969
01:19:26,728 --> 01:19:28,525
He was meticulous...

970
01:19:35,670 --> 01:19:38,730
He was meticulous
in concealing his other life...

971
01:19:39,808 --> 01:19:41,275
...even from me.

972
01:19:44,346 --> 01:19:46,974
Please don't ask me to betray him now.

973
01:19:48,083 --> 01:19:51,917
I'm very sorry.
But we're trying to stop an epidemic.

974
01:19:52,854 --> 01:19:55,755
We know that this disease
can be transmitted by gay sex.

975
01:19:55,957 --> 01:19:58,824
We hope to prove it's also transmitted
by blood products.

976
01:19:58,960 --> 01:20:01,019
Your brother was a blood donor.

977
01:20:01,396 --> 01:20:03,830
And we know that at least one person...

978
01:20:03,899 --> 01:20:06,459
...who got his blood, got the disease.

979
01:20:12,440 --> 01:20:14,135
If you can help us...

980
01:20:14,309 --> 01:20:16,334
...it would be completely confidential.

981
01:20:18,313 --> 01:20:22,306
I'm afraid I can't help you.
I really don't know anything myself.

982
01:20:22,584 --> 01:20:24,484
Here's his stuff.

983
01:20:26,021 --> 01:20:27,545
His mail.

984
01:20:29,024 --> 01:20:30,992
Here's his address book.

985
01:20:31,059 --> 01:20:33,584
You can look through it if you want.
I have.

986
01:20:34,029 --> 01:20:37,192
There's no one in there I don't know.
Nothing unusual.

987
01:20:37,866 --> 01:20:40,130
I wish he would've told me, but he didn't.

988
01:20:42,270 --> 01:20:44,932
Look at this. What about this entry?

989
01:20:48,977 --> 01:20:50,604
"Marc, Repairman"?

990
01:21:00,555 --> 01:21:01,749
Dr. Conant's office.

991
01:21:02,257 --> 01:21:06,159
- Is someone named Marc there?
- This is Dr. Marcus Conant's office.

992
01:21:06,328 --> 01:21:07,852
May I help you?

993
01:21:08,830 --> 01:21:10,593
Sorry, wrong number.

994
01:21:14,402 --> 01:21:16,165
Only for you.

995
01:21:16,338 --> 01:21:20,775
I was the secret doctor he came to
for those messy little problems...

996
01:21:21,576 --> 01:21:24,636
...he couldn't let his family physician
know about.

997
01:21:24,880 --> 01:21:27,474
In 1980, he had a case of K. S...

998
01:21:27,849 --> 01:21:29,339
...pneumocystis...

999
01:21:29,684 --> 01:21:31,413
...the whole bag of horrors.

1000
01:21:33,455 --> 01:21:36,151
Thank you very much. I love you.

1001
01:21:37,292 --> 01:21:39,089
Thanks a lot, Doctor.

1002
01:21:39,461 --> 01:21:42,555
All right,
let the blood banks stonewall this one!

1003
01:21:46,868 --> 01:21:51,999
I'd like to remind everyone that
these are not regulations from the CDC.

1004
01:21:52,073 --> 01:21:55,008
This is a workshop where every agency...

1005
01:21:55,076 --> 01:21:58,910
...connected to the blood industry can
evaluate information the CDC has found.

1006
01:22:00,215 --> 01:22:03,082
We're hoping to be able to arrive
at some course of action.

1007
01:22:03,151 --> 01:22:06,643
One option is to establish guidelines...

1008
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:09,519
...to keep people at high risk
from donating blood.

1009
01:22:09,591 --> 01:22:13,220
Banning homosexuals from giving blood
won't protect the blood supply.

1010
01:22:13,828 --> 01:22:16,695
What it will do is stigmatize them.

1011
01:22:16,865 --> 01:22:20,562
Reminds me of blood banks
rejecting donations from blacks...

1012
01:22:20,635 --> 01:22:22,694
...for fear of syphilis.

1013
01:22:22,771 --> 01:22:26,207
The civil rights implications
of establishing guidelines...

1014
01:22:26,274 --> 01:22:27,605
Civil rights, my ass!

1015
01:22:27,676 --> 01:22:31,544
My son's a hemophiliac and if homosexuals
are infecting the blood supply...

1016
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:33,478
...why not keep them from donating?

1017
01:22:33,548 --> 01:22:37,006
The entire gay community?
Then what? Separate drinking fountains?

1018
01:22:37,085 --> 01:22:39,076
One for gays! One for humans!

1019
01:22:39,154 --> 01:22:41,247
Don't start that gay rights crap!

1020
01:22:41,323 --> 01:22:44,053
There are 20,000 hemophiliacs
in this country...

1021
01:22:44,125 --> 01:22:47,561
...and GRID has become the second
leading cause of death.

1022
01:22:47,629 --> 01:22:50,530
We have rights, too.
One of them is the right to stay alive.

1023
01:22:50,598 --> 01:22:53,567
I know that we're dealing
with a very complex...

1024
01:22:53,735 --> 01:22:55,999
...and a highly emotional issue, but...

1025
01:22:56,071 --> 01:22:58,198
How can you expect us
to be unemotional...

1026
01:22:58,306 --> 01:23:00,866
...when at least one person
is dying every day...

1027
01:23:00,976 --> 01:23:03,843
...from a disease that doesn't
even have a name?

1028
01:23:03,979 --> 01:23:07,346
If the CDC can't bother
to come up with a name...

1029
01:23:07,449 --> 01:23:10,748
...at least it should stop the media
from calling it GRID!

1030
01:23:11,119 --> 01:23:15,886
Enough people hate gays without having
the stigma of this disease placed on us!

1031
01:23:16,491 --> 01:23:21,485
Especially since it's been shown that this
disease is no longer merely gay... related.

1032
01:23:21,896 --> 01:23:25,127
I make a motion
to officially call this disease...

1033
01:23:25,233 --> 01:23:28,327
...Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome...

1034
01:23:28,703 --> 01:23:30,227
...or AIDS.

1035
01:23:33,641 --> 01:23:36,109
Questions or discussions on this issue?

1036
01:23:36,211 --> 01:23:37,610
I second it.

1037
01:23:37,979 --> 01:23:40,413
All in favor of Dr. Voeller's motion.

1038
01:23:43,385 --> 01:23:46,047
And opposed? The motion's carried.

1039
01:23:46,721 --> 01:23:48,018
Dr. Bove?

1040
01:23:48,189 --> 01:23:51,750
The FDA Advisory Panel
to the blood banks feels that...

1041
01:23:51,926 --> 01:23:55,157
...the evidence for nearly all of this
is inferential.

1042
01:23:55,263 --> 01:23:59,393
The CDC's evidence of blood
transmission cannot be warranted...

1043
01:23:59,501 --> 01:24:04,734
...until the CDC shows definitively that
an infectious agent causes this disease.

1044
01:24:05,006 --> 01:24:08,237
Nothing about it exists
in the peer... reviewed medical literature!

1045
01:24:08,343 --> 01:24:10,208
Not one case!

1046
01:24:10,545 --> 01:24:13,013
Evidence of such
blood transmission is lacking.

1047
01:24:13,114 --> 01:24:17,608
May I point out that the blood industry
is under the jurisdiction of the FDA...

1048
01:24:17,685 --> 01:24:21,382
...and according to Dr. Bove, they don't
acknowledge there is an epidemic.

1049
01:24:21,489 --> 01:24:25,152
Because there is no evidence
that it's a blood... borne disease.

1050
01:24:25,260 --> 01:24:27,820
Suppose, for example,
a small amount of blood...

1051
01:24:27,996 --> 01:24:31,056
...by some unlikely chance,
is contaminated.

1052
01:24:31,232 --> 01:24:35,498
With no test to find out which blood
is safe and which isn't, what should we do?

1053
01:24:35,904 --> 01:24:38,270
Destroy the entire blood supply
in America...

1054
01:24:38,339 --> 01:24:42,298
...because some of it may
or may not be contaminated?

1055
01:24:42,444 --> 01:24:44,036
No.

1056
01:24:44,212 --> 01:24:47,943
In fact, testing is the second option
that we should discuss.

1057
01:24:48,750 --> 01:24:52,686
We at the CDC have found
that the hepatitis B test...

1058
01:24:53,721 --> 01:24:58,658
...is 88 percent effective
in identifying patients with this disease.

1059
01:24:59,060 --> 01:25:01,790
Is the CDC suggesting
that the blood industry...

1060
01:25:01,896 --> 01:25:05,957
...spend $100 million a year
to use a test for the wrong disease...

1061
01:25:06,034 --> 01:25:10,596
...because of a handful of transfusion
fatalities and eight dead hemophiliacs?

1062
01:25:10,872 --> 01:25:13,033
How many dead hemophiliacs
do you need?

1063
01:25:14,075 --> 01:25:16,805
How many people have to die
to make it cost efficient...

1064
01:25:16,945 --> 01:25:18,810
...for you to do something about it?

1065
01:25:19,514 --> 01:25:21,846
A hundred? A thousand?

1066
01:25:22,350 --> 01:25:24,818
Give us a number
so we won't annoy you again...

1067
01:25:24,919 --> 01:25:27,752
...until the money you begin spending
on lawsuits...

1068
01:25:27,889 --> 01:25:31,916
...makes it more profitable for you
to save people than to kill them!

1069
01:25:50,612 --> 01:25:54,048
The disease called AIDS,
Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome...

1070
01:25:54,115 --> 01:25:56,606
...sounds less than deadly,
more like a diet pill.

1071
01:25:56,718 --> 01:25:58,481
Medical researchers are warning...

1072
01:25:58,586 --> 01:26:00,577
The risk of contracting AIDS...

1073
01:26:00,788 --> 01:26:04,155
Henry Pinya, who has AIDS,
got into a minor traffic accident.

1074
01:26:04,325 --> 01:26:07,294
Police called the Hazardous
Materials Team.

1075
01:26:07,729 --> 01:26:10,721
The impact on blood banks
could be disastrous.

1076
01:26:11,199 --> 01:26:14,464
Doctors learned today that
at least one hemophiliac patient...

1077
01:26:14,602 --> 01:26:17,503
...was given blood plasma from a donor
who died of AIDS.

1078
01:26:17,705 --> 01:26:21,266
Possible association of AIDS
and blood transfusion...

1079
01:26:21,376 --> 01:26:23,742
...is of the order of one in a million.

1080
01:26:26,114 --> 01:26:30,312
I've been looking all over for you.
I just talked to Paul O'Mally.

1081
01:26:30,552 --> 01:26:33,043
He's wrapping up the hepatitis B study
and listen:

1082
01:26:33,188 --> 01:26:36,157
12 of the first 24 cases of AIDS
in this country...

1083
01:26:36,291 --> 01:26:40,785
...are men that we've been tracking for
hepatitis B every year since 1978.

1084
01:26:41,429 --> 01:26:46,526
We've been talking about using the test,
but forgot about the hepatitis B study.

1085
01:26:46,734 --> 01:26:50,101
- Congratulations.
- You don't think this is important?

1086
01:26:50,171 --> 01:26:54,198
30,000 blood samples and detailed
questionnaires from 7,000 gay men...

1087
01:26:54,342 --> 01:26:59,109
...from five cities, taken every year since
three years before the epidemic broke out.

1088
01:26:59,180 --> 01:27:02,809
We've got the natural history
of the epidemic in a freezer in Phoenix.

1089
01:27:02,884 --> 01:27:04,044
I know the study.

1090
01:27:04,118 --> 01:27:07,178
You're saying we should pull
the samples and organize them.

1091
01:27:07,255 --> 01:27:11,191
- Where will we get the money to do that?
- Juggle or steal it.

1092
01:27:11,259 --> 01:27:14,387
There's nothing to juggle or steal.
There's no money, none.

1093
01:27:14,762 --> 01:27:17,890
The $866,000 budget that we requested
a year ago...

1094
01:27:17,999 --> 01:27:20,524
...for the task force
still hasn't been approved.

1095
01:27:20,602 --> 01:27:24,003
Where do you think we'll get the money
to do a job as massive as this?

1096
01:27:24,072 --> 01:27:25,630
That's your job.

1097
01:27:25,807 --> 01:27:29,607
How am I supposed to do my job
with you shooting your mouth off?

1098
01:27:29,677 --> 01:27:30,666
What?

1099
01:27:30,745 --> 01:27:35,375
Your outburst at the blood bank meeting
damaged the credibility of the CDC.

1100
01:27:51,499 --> 01:27:54,525
The only way we'll get the blood banks
to start testing...

1101
01:27:54,602 --> 01:27:59,096
...is if we find somebody with enough clout
they've got God's unlisted phone number.

1102
01:27:59,307 --> 01:28:01,241
Which these people do.

1103
01:28:01,676 --> 01:28:03,610
Jesus, this is proof.

1104
01:28:03,911 --> 01:28:06,880
Why haven't they sued somebody,
raised hell?

1105
01:28:06,981 --> 01:28:10,417
Publicity, litigation,
pictures in the tabloids.

1106
01:28:10,818 --> 01:28:13,651
My dear young man, it simply is not done.

1107
01:28:13,788 --> 01:28:17,417
If you can convince them how many lives
they'll save if they go public...

1108
01:28:17,492 --> 01:28:20,950
...that comes under the heading
of public service which they are big on.

1109
01:28:21,029 --> 01:28:22,053
If!

1110
01:28:22,363 --> 01:28:25,025
...might be of some assistance to us.

1111
01:28:25,533 --> 01:28:27,933
I'm sorry, but I don't understand.

1112
01:28:28,303 --> 01:28:32,433
Complications of all kinds
are quite common after heart surgery.

1113
01:28:32,807 --> 01:28:36,573
What could my case
possibly have to do with AIDS?

1114
01:28:39,113 --> 01:28:40,410
They didn't tell you?

1115
01:28:41,282 --> 01:28:42,613
Tell me what?

1116
01:28:42,984 --> 01:28:44,747
We thought we'd heard everything.

1117
01:28:46,521 --> 01:28:47,852
My God.

1118
01:28:49,157 --> 01:28:50,852
I'm sorry.

1119
01:29:00,835 --> 01:29:03,326
I have here your medical records.

1120
01:29:06,874 --> 01:29:08,671
You're aware that...

1121
01:29:08,843 --> 01:29:13,644
...during your surgery you were given
20 units of blood from Irwin Memorial?

1122
01:29:16,551 --> 01:29:17,984
We know that.

1123
01:29:19,921 --> 01:29:23,982
When you started getting all these
bizarre diseases, one after another...

1124
01:29:25,293 --> 01:29:27,693
Didn't your doctors tell you why?

1125
01:29:27,962 --> 01:29:31,125
We've had so many doctors.

1126
01:29:31,299 --> 01:29:35,531
None of them had
any specific explanation, just...

1127
01:29:36,270 --> 01:29:39,137
...severe complications due to surgery.

1128
01:29:44,812 --> 01:29:47,372
I have here a letter
from one doctor to another...

1129
01:29:47,448 --> 01:29:52,147
...at the University of California Medical
Center, where you had your surgery.

1130
01:29:53,087 --> 01:29:56,352
"We have discovered
that one of her blood donors...

1131
01:29:56,791 --> 01:29:58,918
"...is an AIDS patient."

1132
01:30:11,539 --> 01:30:13,131
May I?

1133
01:31:03,024 --> 01:31:04,218
No.

1134
01:31:14,068 --> 01:31:17,060
Every blood bank in the country
has known for some time...

1135
01:31:17,171 --> 01:31:21,835
...that some of the blood it has been using
for transfusions is contaminated.

1136
01:31:24,579 --> 01:31:27,275
We've been unable to get them
to start testing...

1137
01:31:27,348 --> 01:31:30,146
...or to take any precautions whatsoever.

1138
01:31:30,384 --> 01:31:31,908
I'm terribly sorry.

1139
01:31:34,922 --> 01:31:36,617
Are you telling me...

1140
01:31:36,724 --> 01:31:41,161
...they knew they were giving AIDS
to people and continued to do it?

1141
01:31:51,005 --> 01:31:55,135
We've had extensive discussion
on the subject and as of May 1...

1142
01:31:55,209 --> 01:31:58,076
...Irwin Memorial will begin testing
for antibodies...

1143
01:31:58,145 --> 01:32:00,613
...to the core of the hepatitis B virus.

1144
01:32:03,150 --> 01:32:04,549
Good.

1145
01:32:04,852 --> 01:32:08,447
This is the test we've been urging you
for a year to use...

1146
01:32:08,589 --> 01:32:10,580
...until a better test comes along.

1147
01:32:10,658 --> 01:32:15,061
Not good. That test is not totally effective.

1148
01:32:15,363 --> 01:32:18,730
You're forcing the Red Cross
to start using it, too...

1149
01:32:18,900 --> 01:32:20,800
...or we can't compete.

1150
01:32:21,102 --> 01:32:25,300
Absolutely. We are not convinced
that it's transmitted by transfusion at all.

1151
01:32:25,439 --> 01:32:27,600
What does it take to convince you?

1152
01:32:27,708 --> 01:32:29,938
The CDC confirmed...

1153
01:32:30,111 --> 01:32:34,343
...that the number of transfusion cases
has quadrupled in the past eight months.

1154
01:32:34,949 --> 01:32:36,974
You know you can't prove that.

1155
01:32:37,118 --> 01:32:39,109
Technically, you're right.

1156
01:32:39,520 --> 01:32:42,648
But 89 percent of severe hemophiliacs...

1157
01:32:42,723 --> 01:32:45,624
...who had the most transfusions
have become infected.

1158
01:32:45,993 --> 01:32:47,893
89 percent!

1159
01:32:48,629 --> 01:32:52,588
I find it very hard to equate these figures...

1160
01:32:52,733 --> 01:32:55,224
...with the possible loss in revenue!

1161
01:32:57,471 --> 01:33:00,838
I make a motion that FDA
regulations require...

1162
01:33:01,008 --> 01:33:05,308
...the hepatitis B test be used
to screen all blood and blood products...

1163
01:33:05,379 --> 01:33:07,813
...before they're used on patients.

1164
01:33:08,482 --> 01:33:10,040
Second.

1165
01:33:10,518 --> 01:33:11,780
In favor?

1166
01:33:13,354 --> 01:33:14,582
Opposed?

1167
01:33:17,024 --> 01:33:18,753
Motion not carried.

1168
01:33:22,096 --> 01:33:23,859
Let me ask you this:

1169
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:28,535
When doctors start
acting like businessmen...

1170
01:33:29,036 --> 01:33:31,869
...who can the people turn to for doctors?

1171
01:33:39,347 --> 01:33:40,507
Jesus!

1172
01:33:41,816 --> 01:33:44,444
Every day I plan to buy some groceries.

1173
01:33:44,518 --> 01:33:46,679
I drive by each night on my way home...

1174
01:33:46,821 --> 01:33:49,984
...and no matter how late it is,
you're always up working.

1175
01:33:50,057 --> 01:33:51,991
You want pasta salad, melon?

1176
01:33:52,059 --> 01:33:53,219
Melon.

1177
01:33:55,630 --> 01:33:56,995
Anything new?

1178
01:33:57,565 --> 01:33:58,930
Any hope? Anywhere?

1179
01:33:59,200 --> 01:34:00,531
Of anything?

1180
01:34:00,601 --> 01:34:03,502
Reagan still hasn't
said the word "AIDS" in public.

1181
01:34:03,571 --> 01:34:06,062
I'm not asking about miracles.

1182
01:34:07,408 --> 01:34:10,536
I think the only hope we have...

1183
01:34:10,945 --> 01:34:12,845
...is the election's coming up...

1184
01:34:13,080 --> 01:34:15,640
...and with the whole country in a panic...

1185
01:34:15,716 --> 01:34:19,243
...even the Moral Majority is
on Reagan's ass to do something quick.

1186
01:34:19,654 --> 01:34:23,112
Sure he will,
the same old political smoke and mirrors.

1187
01:34:24,492 --> 01:34:28,519
A friend of mine sneaked me
a memo from the White House...

1188
01:34:29,530 --> 01:34:32,465
...claiming they've already spent
$26 million on:

1189
01:34:32,767 --> 01:34:36,669
"Studies relevant to patients with AIDS."

1190
01:34:37,538 --> 01:34:40,405
If they spend $10 million on research
for the common cold...

1191
01:34:40,474 --> 01:34:44,808
...they call it relevant because in both
cases the immune system breaks down.

1192
01:34:45,346 --> 01:34:47,576
The truth is, out of that $26 million...

1193
01:34:48,115 --> 01:34:51,949
...only $750,000 has actually been spent
on AIDS research.

1194
01:34:53,521 --> 01:34:56,354
What happened to the rest, I have no idea.

1195
01:34:57,625 --> 01:34:59,684
- Hello.
