The man who discovered the virus...

1432
01:54:10,009 --> 01:54:14,275
...which causes AIDS, excuse me...

1433
01:54:14,547 --> 01:54:18,711
...is our eminent Dr. Robert Gallo.

1434
01:54:23,723 --> 01:54:26,419
Thank you, Secretary Heckler.

1435
01:54:27,827 --> 01:54:31,786
I should start and be brief by saying that...

1436
01:54:31,965 --> 01:54:35,196
...there are obviously
other major contributors.

1437
01:54:35,802 --> 01:54:39,704
In our own group,
I have to mention someone...

1438
01:54:40,373 --> 01:54:45,208
...who came to us from Czechoslovakia,
Dr. Mika Popovic.

1439
01:54:45,712 --> 01:54:49,045
A lot of this couldn't have been done
without the previous support...

1440
01:54:49,115 --> 01:54:53,814
...from the Cancer Institute
on the earlier HTLV isolates.

1441
01:54:54,520 --> 01:54:57,455
I've seen discussions
about the work in Paris.

1442
01:54:58,558 --> 01:55:02,756
There was, there is not,
there never has been...

1443
01:55:03,796 --> 01:55:07,698
...fights or controversies between us
and the group in France.

1444
01:55:07,867 --> 01:55:11,997
I came back from a meeting
astonished to see this kind of discussion.

1445
01:55:12,538 --> 01:55:15,439
The laboratory at the Pasteur Institute
and my laboratory...

1446
01:55:15,541 --> 01:55:17,668
...have been friends for about 15 years.

1447
01:55:17,844 --> 01:55:19,402
We are in fact collaborating.

1448
01:55:20,580 --> 01:55:22,138
I can't watch.

1449
01:55:24,851 --> 01:55:29,049
Phase One is finished. We've found
the virus, we're working on a blood test.

1450
01:55:29,389 --> 01:55:31,823
This is my proposal for Phase Two:

1451
01:55:32,525 --> 01:55:34,823
Prevention, education and cure.

1452
01:55:35,395 --> 01:55:36,953
If that goes through...

1453
01:55:37,096 --> 01:55:41,328
...I wanna be transferred to San Francisco
and work on it from there.

1454
01:55:42,769 --> 01:55:45,636
$37 million a year?

1455
01:55:45,939 --> 01:55:48,305
- That's totally unrealistic.
- It's not.

1456
01:55:48,608 --> 01:55:49,836
It's cheap.

1457
01:55:49,976 --> 01:55:53,969
It's about 15 cents per person
to make the entire population safer.

1458
01:55:54,280 --> 01:55:57,272
- It's what's needed.
- I'm sure it is, but you won't get it.

1459
01:55:57,350 --> 01:56:00,046
If you ask for this much, you'll get nothing.

1460
01:56:00,119 --> 01:56:03,213
- Try to re... figure for $4 million...
- I won't re... figure it.

1461
01:56:03,289 --> 01:56:05,917
It's an honest report.
I want you to send it in.

1462
01:56:05,992 --> 01:56:09,257
I'm tryin' to tell you
you're going about this the wrong way.

1463
01:56:09,329 --> 01:56:14,266
It's cheap. Wait a few years, and we'll
be talking about billions in health care.

1464
01:56:20,773 --> 01:56:22,365
I'll send it in.

1465
01:56:23,309 --> 01:56:26,574
Four more years.

1466
01:56:27,947 --> 01:56:28,936
Thank you.

1467
01:56:29,482 --> 01:56:31,643
Thank you all very much.

1468
01:56:36,789 --> 01:56:39,485
It seems we did this four years ago.

1469
01:56:43,629 --> 01:56:47,565
Nancy and I would like to express...

1470
01:56:50,169 --> 01:56:51,761
Nancy!

1471
01:56:53,006 --> 01:56:56,339
This is not a political issue,
this is a health issue.

1472
01:56:56,542 --> 01:56:59,306
This is not a gay issue,
this is a human issue.

1473
01:56:59,379 --> 01:57:03,179
Had this disease afflicted children or
members of the Chamber of Commerce...

1474
01:57:03,282 --> 01:57:06,479
...the Reagan administration
would've broken down all doors...

1475
01:57:06,586 --> 01:57:09,817
...in order to push the government
on all fronts to deal with it.

1476
01:57:10,089 --> 01:57:13,752
I came here today in the hope
that my epitaph would not read:

1477
01:57:14,293 --> 01:57:16,090
"I died of red tape."

1478
01:57:16,295 --> 01:57:17,922
Four more years!

1479
01:58:25,131 --> 01:58:27,827
Can I get a coffee and a jelly donut?

1480
01:58:35,708 --> 01:58:38,438
Are you coming from work
or going to work?

1481
01:58:38,778 --> 01:58:40,109
Going to.

1482
01:58:40,780 --> 01:58:41,838
You?

1483
01:58:43,516 --> 01:58:45,143
I couldn't sleep.

1484
01:58:47,553 --> 01:58:50,647
I heard your Phase Two proposal
was turned down.

1485
01:58:51,524 --> 01:58:53,458
Officially, "too expensive."

1486
01:58:53,559 --> 01:58:56,426
Unofficially,
and they say this diplomatically:

1487
01:58:56,696 --> 01:58:59,597
"You should look busy and do nothing."

1488
01:59:02,668 --> 01:59:05,603
Was that meant to be diplomatic,
how you just told me?

1489
01:59:06,539 --> 01:59:08,871
It was meant to sound angry.

1490
01:59:09,575 --> 01:59:11,167
At me or at you?

1491
01:59:11,410 --> 01:59:12,934
At me?

1492
01:59:13,713 --> 01:59:14,975
Why me?

1493
01:59:15,815 --> 01:59:19,615
I don't know. I guess, both. All right?

1494
01:59:20,887 --> 01:59:23,447
Sometimes I look at you
in awe and wonder.

1495
01:59:24,423 --> 01:59:25,720
I mean it.

1496
01:59:25,992 --> 01:59:29,291
How you wind your way through
bureaucratic bullshit every day...

1497
01:59:29,395 --> 01:59:31,056
...and never get a drop on you.

1498
01:59:31,130 --> 01:59:34,156
- How do you do it?
- By not asking questions like that.

1499
01:59:34,300 --> 01:59:36,393
Insult me if you like, directly...

1500
01:59:36,502 --> 01:59:40,268
...but don't insult both of us by disguising
this as some kind of compliment.

1501
01:59:40,540 --> 01:59:42,906
Insult you? How?

1502
01:59:43,476 --> 01:59:45,910
The awe and the wonder? I mean it.

1503
01:59:50,049 --> 01:59:52,779
I asked the Second Floor for a transfer.

1504
01:59:53,986 --> 01:59:56,045
Can you help push it through?

1505
01:59:56,222 --> 01:59:58,315
I already have. It's done.

1506
02:00:00,493 --> 02:00:03,189
Really? Where to?

1507
02:00:04,397 --> 02:00:07,833
- How do you want this, diplomatically?
- I've gotten used to angry.

1508
02:00:07,934 --> 02:00:09,128
San Francisco.

1509
02:00:10,236 --> 02:00:11,828
Reward or exile?

1510
02:00:18,044 --> 02:00:21,844
If you hate it, why spend your entire career
working for the government?

1511
02:00:25,918 --> 02:00:29,786
Remember what Willie Sutton said when
they asked him why he robbed banks?

1512
02:00:29,855 --> 02:00:33,188
"Because that's where the money is."
This is where the diseases are.

1513
02:00:34,694 --> 02:00:36,093
Bugs.

1514
02:00:41,968 --> 02:00:45,495
Sometimes I look at you
with awe and wonder.

1515
02:01:11,831 --> 02:01:13,423
There it is.

1516
02:01:14,267 --> 02:01:16,758
A little cake for the maverick among us.

1517
02:01:16,836 --> 02:01:19,464
Something the boys
in the retroviral lab whipped up.

1518
02:01:27,613 --> 02:01:31,379
Excuse me, can I speak to you alone
for a second, please?

1519
02:01:37,023 --> 02:01:38,456
You might need this.

1520
02:01:41,494 --> 02:01:43,587
That's great, they're rose... colored.

1521
02:01:44,463 --> 02:01:46,795
- Definitely you.
- Well done.

1522
02:01:47,266 --> 02:01:48,631
Looks good.

1523
02:01:51,737 --> 02:01:54,501
- To Don Francis.
- Long may he live.

1524
02:01:55,308 --> 02:01:57,435
- Speech!
- Say something.

1525
02:02:03,449 --> 02:02:06,247
I got a call from
our Washington lawyer.

1526
02:02:06,819 --> 02:02:08,810
Gallo got the patent
for the blood test.

1527
02:02:09,455 --> 02:02:12,982
Even though we applied five months
before him.

1528
02:02:13,759 --> 02:02:17,923
Here's Gallo's virus which is
almost identical to ours.

1529
02:02:18,497 --> 02:02:19,725
Look at the photo.

1530
02:02:19,999 --> 02:02:23,730
It's a picture of our virus LAV,
which he calls his virus...

1531
02:02:23,969 --> 02:02:25,960
...and names it HTLVIII.

1532
02:02:27,340 --> 02:02:33,245
The only way to compare one virus
to another is by DNA.

1533
02:02:37,883 --> 02:02:44,584
Put together a team to break
the genetic code of both viruses.

1534
02:02:46,058 --> 02:02:47,855
This time he's gone too far.

1535
02:02:56,502 --> 02:03:00,233
The genes of any two different isolates
of the same virus...

1536
02:03:00,673 --> 02:03:05,303
...are expected to deviate from each other,
usually by 6 to 20 percent.

1537
02:03:05,745 --> 02:03:12,309
The genetic sequence
of Dr. Gallo's HTLVIII prototype isolate...

1538
02:03:12,785 --> 02:03:17,154
...varies from our virus, called LAV...

1539
02:03:17,423 --> 02:03:19,357
...by less than 1 percent.

1540
02:03:19,859 --> 02:03:23,295
They are identical to a degree that would
not be anticipated...

1541
02:03:23,362 --> 02:03:26,923
...from any two isolates
from the same family.

1542
02:03:28,701 --> 02:03:30,032
Thank you.

1543
02:03:30,169 --> 02:03:32,933
Are you suggesting that Gallo
stole it from the French?

1544
02:03:33,339 --> 02:03:37,139
I think that question would
best be answered by someone else.

1545
02:03:43,082 --> 02:03:46,142
Excuse me,
I'm not quite sure what he was saying.

1546
02:03:46,786 --> 02:03:50,882
The virus Gallo has
is the same kind the French have?

1547
02:03:51,390 --> 02:03:56,453
Not the same kind. It's the same virus
exactly, from the same patient.

1548
02:04:21,420 --> 02:04:22,682
You okay?

1549
02:04:25,191 --> 02:04:26,453
Sit down.

1550
02:04:35,134 --> 02:04:37,227
Should I call an ambulance?

1551
02:04:39,839 --> 02:04:41,500
Stay there.

1552
02:05:13,739 --> 02:05:15,206
I just heard.

1553
02:05:16,342 --> 02:05:17,741
Let's go up.

1554
02:05:34,026 --> 02:05:35,789
Hello.

1555
02:05:38,764 --> 02:05:40,163
This is Don.

1556
02:05:41,767 --> 02:05:43,394
Nice to meet you.

1557
02:05:44,803 --> 02:05:46,532
Look who's here.

1558
02:05:46,839 --> 02:05:48,238
Is that Don?

1559
02:05:49,775 --> 02:05:51,367
There's two of you.

1560
02:05:52,845 --> 02:05:55,905
We're both Don,
don't ask me which is which.

1561
02:06:03,055 --> 02:06:07,287
One moment he's talking perfectly
coherently, the next he's talking gibberish.

1562
02:06:08,961 --> 02:06:12,829
I'm gonna take Kico for a cup of coffee.
You wanna join us?

1563
02:06:14,300 --> 02:06:17,292
- No, I think...
- I'll be back in a minute.

1564
02:07:24,703 --> 02:07:27,900
Would you hand me my...

1565
02:07:34,913 --> 02:07:36,141
Glasses?

1566
02:07:47,626 --> 02:07:49,526
Am I talking gibberish?

1567
02:07:50,462 --> 02:07:52,430
No, not to me.

1568
02:08:01,874 --> 02:08:03,967
This didn't have to happen.

1569
02:08:06,078 --> 02:08:07,978
We could've stopped it.

1570
02:08:09,515 --> 02:08:11,107
Can you still?

1571
02:08:13,652 --> 02:08:15,620
Can we still stop it?

1572
02:08:16,755 --> 02:08:18,222
I don't know.

1573
02:08:21,827 --> 02:08:25,729
I used to be afraid of dying.

1574
02:08:28,333 --> 02:08:30,096
I'm not anymore.

1575
02:08:31,537 --> 02:08:34,836
I'm more afraid of what happens...

1576
02:08:37,242 --> 02:08:39,870
...to the people who live.

1577
02:21:42,242 --> 02:21:43,870
{{{the end}}}

